<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Eight women entrepreneurs <a href="//www.fastcompany.com/3033532/hit-the-ground-running/8-women-entrepreneurs-share-how-they-conquered-their-biggest-roadbloc?%28Fast+Company%29">share how</a> they conquered their biggest roadblocks.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Here&#8217;s why accounting firms <a href="//www.accountingtoday.com/news/mergers-acquisitions/why-cpa-firms-gobble-each-other-to-grow-71475-1.html">gobble each other</a> to grow.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Smith &amp; Wesson is <a href="//www.foxbusiness.com/industries/2014/07/28/smith-wesson-fined-2m-over-foreign-bribery-charges/">fined $2 million</a> over foreign bribery charges.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Retail</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ A study projects that 19 percent of American retail e-commerce sales <a href="//www.mobilemarketingwatch.com/retail-reality-mobile-sales-sites-grab-more-moola-than-apps-43627/">will come from</a> mobile devices this year.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Amazon <a href="//www.foxbusiness.com/industries/2014/07/28/amazon-offers-3d-printing-to-customize-earrings-bobble-head-toys/">will offer</a> 3-D printing services that allow customers to customize offerings from third-party sellers.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Around the Country</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Detroit shuts off water to residents <a href="//www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2014/07/26/detroit-shuts-off-water-to-residents-but-not-to-businesses-who-owe-millions.html">but not to</a> businesses who owe money to the city.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Milwaukee small-business owners <a href="//www.biztimes.com/article/20140728/ENEWSLETTERS02/140729822/-1/daily_enews/Milwaukee-small-business-owners-give-state-C+">give their state</a> a C+.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Philadelphia gets a D in &#8220;<a href="//m.bizjournals.com/philadelphia/morning_roundup/2014/07/philadelphia-small-business.html">small-business friendliness</a>.&#8221;</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Sam Adams <a href="//www.kplctv.com/story/26130208/samuel-adams-brewing-the-american-dream-hosts-speed-coaching-for-seattles-small-business-community">brings its</a> speed-coaching to Seattle.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ After a fire, the owner of a Wisconsin restaurant <a href="//www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/07/25/bruce-kroll-culvers_n_5617555.html">continued paying</a> his staff during the six months it took to rebuild.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Around the World</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Only the very brave, or foolish, <a href="//qz.com/241245/only-the-very-brave-or-foolish-are-investing-in-russia-right-now/">are investing</a> in Russia right now.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ The owner of an Australian tour company <a href="https://au.news.yahoo.com/a/24563069/tourists-flee-drunk-aggressive-tour-guide-in-darwin-tour-company-owner-apologises/">has to apologize</a> to customers who fled their âdrunk and aggressiveâ tour guide.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ These are the countries <a href="//mashable.com/2014/07/28/human-progress-development/?u">where human progress</a> is fastest and slowest.</p>
